## Infrastructure Boundaries

This project uses a two-layer environment configuration for worktree compatibility:

- **`.env.example`** (committed) — Reference file showing all required env vars. Copy to `.env`.
- **`.env`** (gitignored) — Working environment. Shared infrastructure defaults (Docker service
  hosts/ports). Do not put secrets here in production.
- **`.env.local`** (gitignored) — Worktree-specific overrides: database suffix, Redis namespace,
  app port. Each worktree has its own copy.

**Boot sequence:**
1. `docker compose up -d` — start shared services (once, not per worktree)
2. `.env.local` is read automatically — sets DB suffix, Redis namespace, port
3. `{{DEV_COMMAND}}` — start the app

**Adding new infrastructure:** New Docker services or external dependencies must follow the
`.env` boundary pattern: shared config in `.env`, worktree-varying config in `.env.local`.
This requires an ADR (see architecture-review Infrastructure trigger).

## Memory

Project memory is stored in `.memory/`. Every session starts with recall.
